9 An Act relating to Service Oklahoma; amending 47 O.S.
2021, Section 1104, as last amended by Section 18,
10 Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
1104), which relates to apportionment; amending,
11 merging, consolidating, and repealing multiple
versions of statute; modifying termination date of
12 certain apportionment; updating statutory language;
repealing 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104, as last amended
13 by Section 7, Chapter 171, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1104), which relates to apportionment;
14 and declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1104, as
19 last amended by Section 18, Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
20 2025, Section 1104), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 1104. A. Unless otherwise provided by law, all fees,
22 taxes, and penalties collected or received pursuant to the Oklahoma
23 Vehicle License and Registration Act or Section 1-101 et seq. of
24 this title shall be apportioned and distributed monthly by the
SB1239 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Okla homa Tax Commission Service Oklahoma in accordance with this
2 section. Service Oklahoma shall provide to the Oklahoma Tax
3 Commission monthly reports of motor vehicle collection information,
4 including, but not limited to, motor vehicle monthly apportionment
5 information, refunds, canceled vouchers, waste tire collections,
6 organ donor program amounts, driver license records, prorate
7 amounts, and sales tax amounts. The reports shall be delivered
8 electronically pursuant to the current calendar year apportionment
9 disbursement schedule provided to Service Oklahoma by the Oklahoma
10 Tax Commission on or before December 1st 1 annually.
11 One percent (1%) of the monies referred to in this section shall
12 be apportioned to the Licensed Operator Performance Fund created in
13 Section 3-106 of this title, in accordance with the applicable
14 metrics determined by Service Oklahoma.
