3 2. The monies apportioned pursuant to subparagraphs a through e
4 of paragraph 1 of this subsection shall be apportioned as follows:
5 forty percent (40%) of such sum shall be distributed to the various
6 counties in that proportion which the county road mileage of each
7 county bears to the entire state road mileage as certified by the
8 Transportation Commission and the remaining sixty percent (60%) of
9 such sum shall be distributed to the various counties on the basis
10 in the proportion which the population and area of each county bears
11 to the total population and area of the state. The population shall
12 be as shown by the last Federal Decennial Census or the most recent
13 annual estimate provided by the United States Bureau of the Census.
14 The funds shall be used for the purpose of constructing and
15 maintaining county highways; provided, however, the county treasurer
16 may deposit so much of the funds in the sinking fund as may be
17 necessary for the retirement of interest and annual accrual of
18 indebtedness created by the issuance of county or township bonds for
19 road purposes. Such deposits to the sinking fund shall not exceed
20 forty percent (40%) of the funds allocated to a county pursuant to
21 this paragraph.
